Package CPS

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Building
    This is an abstract class used for buildings that have an owner, and is derived from AbstractBuilding class.
    CPSException  
    House
    A class to store a house with color and number of rooms information, as well as other properties from super classes.
    Market
    A class to represent a market with closing and Opening hours information in 24 hour format, as well as other properties from super classes.
    Office
    A class to represent an office with job type information, as well as other properties from super classes.
    PlayGround
    This is an abstract class used t represent a playground, which is building 2 meters high by default, and is derived from AbstractBuilding class.
    Street
    This class represents a city with a two sided street.
    Street.AbstractBuilding
    Abstract class to be the super class of every building object in the street.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Street.Mode
    Enum to represent the modes of the program
    Street.Side
    Enum to reoresent the sides of the streets
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CPSException.InvalidDimensionsException
    Thrown when either the height or the length of a building is invalid.
    CPSException.InvalidNumOfRoomsException
    Thrown when the number of rooms entered is invalid.
    CPSException.InvalidPositionException
    Thrown when an invalid position is entered.
    CPSException.InvalidTimeException
    Thrown when invalid hours and minutes are entered.
    CPSException.PlaceIsOccupiedException
    Thrown when a building is being placed on top of another one in the same side.
    CPSException.ReadOnlyException
    Thrown when a modification is made in read only mode.
    CPSException.SetHeightNotSupportedException
    Thrown when the building has a default non-editable height.
